The Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Niger State Chapter has urged its residents to remain united irrespective of religious and political ideologies to guarantee peaceful coexistence in the state. In the Sallah message, signed by the group’s Media Aide Daniel Atori, the State CAN Chairman, Rev Bulus Dauwa Yohanna said charity, fear of God, and love for one another should dominate the daily affairs of Nigerians to achieve the desired progress, peace and unity. He said, “I would like to use the medium to implore all Nigerlites to see themselves as one, irrespective of religious and political ideologies, to guarantee peaceful coexistence, one united and indivisible people.”